snippet.description:
vvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvv (*NEW*) DIY astral projection formula vvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvv

Take your consciousness out of your body and into the astral plane with this simple meditation. It definitively works, if it doesn't give you vibrations the first time, try try again.

PRACTICE ON YOUR OWN:
You have to keep your awareness pin pointed and focused on your intent to project, without having any thoughts about it. Its hard to explain how to do this unless you have achieved the vibrational stage once before, which is the point of the video. It helps you achieve this state so that you can do it later on your own, it is not meant to help you have a full projection.

Practice meditation, that is coming into, what I like to call, the future-present moment, that is NOW, which almost all awareness of NOW is actually the past, it has already happened. When you click into the now, you sort of feel a WHOOSH in your head. You notice this when you are in danger or sometimes when someone is yelling at you, or when you are in great pain, etc. However, at least for me, I have a hard time making the future-present, some call it the Tao, last long, however staying in what most people call the present instead of thinking about the past or the projected future, can help you achieve the Tao.

Astral projection is best done an hour or two before sunrise (4:30) you want to move to your couch or meditation room, etc, but not your bed. Then meditate as best as you can. When you are in the Now as best as you can be, your thoughts all stop. If you are thinking, you are not in the Now. You cannot STOP thinking, but you can move into the present and realize you are not the thinker. I sometimes like to do this as a practice to help, think this over and over until you understand (not THINK you understand): "This voice is not you, I am the thinker, you are the observer" After a few minutes of this you might start to realize that the voice that is saying that is NOT you at all, but rather just a voice, and you are the observing presence, listening to that voice, but only with a portion of the awareness available to you. -- Another good practice is to sit down in front of your computer and type something. Realize that the part of you that is coming up with the words and the physical body that is typing is not you, but rather a part of you that you are the observer of. This helps you achieve the dissociation from mind and body needed to become soul and thus leave your body. -- Back to it being 4:30, you are laying (if you choose to lay, support your mid and lower back with a pillow, to hold the curvature of your spine, your head pillow should be mostly supporting the curvature of your neck, I use a down pillow because I can move the bulk of feathers to the lower part of the pillow so it supports only my neck and very little of my head. Bend your left leg so that your left foot is touching just above your right inner knee on the Thy. The right knee should be bent slightly), or sitting, there meditating feeling the Tao, you will notice that the future-present moment WHOOSHES are more frequent here. Your breathings should be constant, not pausing after the out breath or the in breath, in the nose, out the nose, and in again. If you can visualize well, it would be best to walk around your apartment, pick things up, etc etc. If not, look through your inner eye while you are meditating, this will look like an iridescent swirl of colors, for me mostly purple, but it almost has a black quality to it, its very subtle, nothing like http://tinyurl.com/cm7xtab which is what you see when you push on your eyes. The moving colors you see are like amorphous blobs and they almost seem random. This is a good opportunity to practice a skill you need when you are visualizing, to see them with your inner eye and resist the urge to try to look around with the physical ones, this will help you forget your physical eyes and keep your inner eye open which you need for astral projection. Most people close their inner eye with the physical, practice until you can keep it open.-- Here you want to fall asleep, with your inner eye open, and your awareness keen on watching them. You will start to pulsate and buzz, feel almost an electrical feeling, here popping sounds that may be quite startling, and then you will see the room you are in, even through your eyes are closed, you will be floating, and you may even roll, your arms going through your mattress and walls! Now its time to apply a separation technique: http://tinyurl.com/csb9dyh goes with this: http://tinyurl.com/ccjqorz

Now that you are out of your body, there are some simple commands that you can issue to get full control. I call them the 3 C's! "CONTROL NOW! CONSCIOUSNESS NOW! CLARITY NOW" The first allowing you total control over your movements. The second giving you total awareness of self and thus control over Direction. The third giving you total crystal clarity of vision, so that you can see All
snippet.title: Astral Projection Guided Meditation (*EASY*) Oobe w/ Binaural Vibrations

---------------- What are theta brainwaves? ---------------

Theta brainwaves are considered extremely relaxing brainwave activity that is commonly associated with sleep and dreaming. Theta brainwaves are high in amplitude and cycle within the range of 4 -- 8 Hz and are usually generated in the brains right hemisphere. Theta waves kick in when we feel emotional, relaxed, daydreamy, unfocused, or are asleep. Theta brainwaves are generally thought of as the brainwaves that are dominant in people with A.D.D., high levels of relaxation, high levels of creativity, and random thinking. The theta brainwave is considered the brainwave pattern that is dominant in deeply relaxed, dream sleep.

Theta brain waves typically range from 4 Hz to 8 Hz. Theta brain waves are associated with the "subconscious mind" and are usually produced in the right-hemisphere of the brain - as opposed to beta brain waves, which are produced in the left-hemisphere and are associated with the "conscious mind." The brain creates theta brain wave rhythms each time you are in "dream sleep." Also, during R.E.M. [Rapid-Eye Movement] sleep, the brain is full of theta brain wave activity.

Nearly 3/5 of your entire time spent sleeping at night involves the production of theta brain waves in your brain. Many individuals also are able to access theta brain waves when they are: driving for a long stretch on the highway, practicing their meditation routine, using a self-hypnosis recording, or practicing other forms of deep relaxation. When you are able to consciously access the alpha brain waves state, you are just one step away from accessing the depths of theta.

What's cool about theta brain waves is the fact that they allow you to connect with your "subconscious mind." The subconscious mind is the place where all experiences, long-term memories, natural creativity, powerful emotions, spiritual connections, and inspiration are all stored. Think of the "subconscious mind" as one big, infinite storage space for "everything" in your life. The theta brain waves are extremely helpful for healing the body of injury and the mind of diseased-states

741hz Solfeggio Frequencies with a 3hz Delta wave Binaural Beat designed to gently ease you into a deep state of relaxation.  Both frequencies were chosen to help aid in the exploration and reconnecting of the unconscious mind.

•13 - 27 Hz - Promotes focused attention toward external stimuli
•13 - 30 Hz - Problem solving, conscious thinking
•18-24 Hz — Euphoria, can result in headaches, anxiety

---------------- What are beta brainwaves? ---------------

Beta brainwaves are considered "fast brain wave" activity. Beta brainwaves are brainwaves that
cycle within the range of 12 -- 38 Hz and are usually generated in the brain's left-hemisphere.

Beta waves kick in when logically thinking, feeling stressed, and feeling tense. Beta is generally
thought of as a "normal" rhythm and is dominant in people who are alert, anxious, or have their
eyes open. Beta brainwaves are considered to be the normal brainwave pattern in healthy adults.

Most children and teenagers have dominant theta and alpha brainwave patterns. There isn't a
single brain wave pattern is better than the others -- so don't think beta brainwaves are some sort
of miracle that your children need! If you happen to be deficient in the beta brain wave range,
increasing them may feel like a miracle!

--------------Benefits of increasing beta brainwaves-----------

•Ability to think quickly
•Highest levels of focus
•Goal oriented
•Increase in I.Q
•Become more social
•More energy


--------------WARNING-----------

As goes for anything, too much beta activity can be a bad thing. By no means would it be a good idea for you to increase a brainwave that you already have high levels of. In fact, there is a real possibility you may experience the negative effects of beta brainwaves, as they can cause anxiety, muscle tension, paranoia, and other related "stressful" effects.
